<FIRST>r a PM-APAppointment     08-15 0097</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-AP Appointment,0099</SECOND>
<HEAD>New Correspondent Named for Rochester</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hilary Appelman, a newswoman in the
Richmond bureau of The Associated Press, has been named AP
correspondent in Rochester.
   The appointment was announced Monday by Lew Wheaton, AP chief of
bureau for upstate New York.
   Ms. Appelman, 25, joined the AP in Richmond in 1987 after
graduating from Yale University and spending a year in the
Philippines as a Fulbright scholar.
   She is a native of Downers Grove, Ill. In Rochester she succeeds
Randolph Picht, who recently was named AP correspondent in St. Louis.
</TEXT>
