parking lot from the police department in Lake Worth, abou 60 miles
north of Miami, while the child's mother was grocery shopping about
12 blocks away.
   The 7-year-old told police he was imitating the half-man,
half-robot character in the movie ``Robocop.''
   Under a Florida law set to take effect Oct. 1, adults who fail to
secure a loaded weapon that is used by a minor in an accidental
shooting could be charged with a felony. The charge carries up to
five years in prison.
