<FIRST>r a PM-BRF--HelicopterCrash     08-15 0126</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--Helicopter Crash,0131</SECOND>
<HEAD>Army Helicopter Crash Kills 3</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FORT BRAGG, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An Army observation helicopter crashed
and burned in a wooded area of Fort Bragg early today, killing the
three soldiers on board, said a base spokesman.
   The OH-58A Kiowa helicopter was on a routine training mission
when the crash occurred at 12:10 a.m., Maj. Doug Foster said.
   Names of the victims were witheld pending notification of
relatives, Foster said.
   He said an investigation will be conducted to determine the cause
of the accident.
   It was the second wreck in less than a week involving military
aircraft on Fort Bragg.
   On Wednesday night, a C-130 from Dyess Air Force Base, Texas,
crashed during an exercise here, killing one crewmember and injuring
six others.
</TEXT>
