<FIRST>r a PM-WeatherpageWeather     08-15 0418</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0431</SECOND>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Scattered Across Nation</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Summer showers and thunderstorms drenched much of the nation
early today.
   An upper air disturbance over the central Rockies produced
showers and thunderstorms over eastern Colorado and southeast
Wyoming. A thunderstorm at Longmont, Colo., produced wind gusts up
to 50 mph.
   An upper air low pressure system combined with unstable air over
the northern Rockies triggered thunderstorms over western Montana
and the Idaho panhandle. Thunderstorm winds gusted to 66 mph at
Lewiston, Mont., Monday night.
   Elsewhere, showers and thunderstorms were scattered over southern
New England, and thunderstorms with heavy rains developed in humid,
unstable air over Georgia and Alabama. More than 2 inches of rain
fell from a thunderstorm at Rockford, Ala.
   Showers and thunderstorms also continued to be scattered ahead of
a cold front that extended from the upper Great Lakes to the middle
Mississippi Valley.
   Heavier rainfall during the six hours ending at 2 a.m. EDT
included 1} inches at Anniston, Ala., and nearly 1\ inches at
Alpena, Mich.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms over much
of the Atlantic Coast, the central and southern Appalachians and the
Great Lakes; scattered showers and thunderstorms over the northern
Rockies; and showers over northwest Washington state.
   Highs were expected to be in the 60s along southern Lake
Superior; in the 70s in parts of the Dakotas, the upper Mississippi
Valley, the upper Great Lakes, the northern Rockies, the Pacific
Northwest and along the California coast; in the 90s in parts of
Florida, the northern Plains, the western Gulf Coast and the central
Rockies; in the 100s in the desert Southwest and interior valleys of
California; and in the 80s elsewhere.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 42
degrees at Yellowstone Park in Wyoming to 97 degrees at Glendale,
Ariz.
   Other reports:
   EAST _ Atlanta 72 showery; Boston 73 rain; Buffalo 65 fair;
Cleveland 65 fair; Miami 76 partly cloudy; New York 72 cloudy;
Philadelphia 74 cloudy; Portland, Maine 69 foggy; and Washington 72
partly cloudy.
   CENTRAL _ Bismarck 47 fair; Denver 61 fair; Fort Worth 74 cloudy;
Indianapolis 68 foggy; Kansas City 71 partly cloudy; Little Rock 70
foggy; Louisville 69 hazy; Nashville 70 foggy; New Orleans 73 fair;
St. Louis 75 hazy; and Minneapolis 61 cloudy.
   WEST _ Albuquerque 72 cloudy; Las Vegas 92 fair; Portland 60
fair; Salt Lake City 71 fair; San Francisco 59 fair; and Seattle 58
cloudy.
   CANADA _ Montreal 66 fair; and Toronto 66 hazy.
</TEXT>
