<FILEID>AP-NR-08-15-89 1012EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r i PM-Greece-Fires     08-15 0100</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Greece-Fires,0102</SECOND>
<HEAD>Forest Fires Scorch Greek Peninsula</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KHALKIDHIKI, Greece (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hundreds of firefighters backed by
troops and aircraft today battled wildfires sweeping through this
northeastern peninsula popular with tourists.
   An official of the National Forest Fire Control Center said the
fires have destroyed over 1,200 acres of land, mostly forests, since
they started two days ago.
   He said strong northerly winds continued to blow across the
peninsula, fanning the flames.
   Four firefighting planes flew scores of flights, dumping water
and chemicals to stop the flames from spreading.
   There were no reports of injuries, evacuations, or damage to
buildings.
</TEXT>
