<FIRST>r a PM-IvanaSuit     08-15 0176</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Ivana Suit,0181</SECOND>
<HEAD>Mrs. Trump: Ivana My Name</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``Ivana'' has Ivana Trump seeing red, with the
wife of Donald Trump claiming that the lipstick is trading on her
name.
   Mrs. Trump, who runs the Plaza Hotel for her husband, has a name
that has ``become synonymous with the very best, regardless of the
project or activity,'' according to a $10 million lawsuit filed
Monday in federal court.
   Pavion, a Nyack cosmetics company, began selling Ivana lipstick
in March. Stanley Ackers, the company's president, said he did not
have Mrs. Trump in mind and did not name the lipstick after anyone
in particular.
   According to the lawsuit, Pavion tried ``to mislead the trade and
the public into believing that (Mrs.) Trump has either approved or
sponsored the goods.''
   Trump has fought several similar court battles.
   In June, he won a court order barring the Washington-based
International Trading and Finance Co. from calling its moving and
storage subsidiary Trump Shuttle _ a name Trump used weeks later
when he bought the Eastern Shuttle.
</TEXT>
