<FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Germany-Space     08-15 0107</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-BRF--Germany-Space,0111</SECOND>
<HEAD>Space Agency to Try Again on Satellite</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DARMSTADT, West Germany (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The European Space Agency said
Tuesday it would make a fourth attempt to ignite a booster engine
needed to send the Hipparcos satellite into its designated orbit
22,320 miles above Earth.
   The European Space Operations Center in Darmstadt, near
Frankfurt, said the attempt would be made made Thursday.
   The agency's previous attempts to activate the satellite's Apogee
Boost Motor failed. Engineers have been unable to determine why the
booster has failed.
   Hipparcos is designed to provide precise measurements of the
stars.
   The satellite was launched Aug. 9 by the agency's Ariane rocket.
</TEXT>
