<SECOND>PM-BRF--CBS Correspondent,0116</SECOND>
<HEAD>Threlkeld Moves From ABC to CBS</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Richard Threlkeld, a reporter for CBS for 15
years before moving to ABC in 1982, will rejoin his old network as a
national correspondent.
   CBS President David Burke said Threlkeld will assume his new post
later this month.
   Threlkeld's ``class, extraordinary writing abilities and
experience in both domestic and international coverage make him one
of the finest journalists of our time,'' Burke said.
   During the past seven years Threlkeld covered a wide variety of
stories, including the TWA hostage crisis, the U.S. invasion of
Grenada and the Falkland Islands war.
   Threlkeld, 51, will be based in New York.
