<FIRST>r a PM-FamilyMurder     08-15 0258</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Family Murder,0266</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sister, Brother, Mother Charged with Murder</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COEUR D'ALENE, Idaho (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The daughter, son and wife of a man
who was shot to death on the porch of his mobile home were charged
in the slaying, and authorities say the family had plotted his death
for at least a month.
   Investigators have refused to give a motive for the shooting of
Robert Dean ``Bobby'' Bell. But two daughters who aren't charged in
the case, ages 16 and 20, said that Bell had been violent and
abusive to his family for years.
   Bell's daughter, Patricia C. Hylton, 21, and son, Robert Dow
Bell, 22, were charged Monday with murder. They and their mother,
Penny Carr Bell, 43, were charged with solicitation and conspiracy
to commit murder.
   Bell was shot in the back of the neck with a rifle Friday.
   Authorities allege the Robert Dow Bell taught his sister, Ms.
Hylton, how to use the gun and that she fired the shot.
   An informant had told authorities that the defendants asked him
last month where they could get poison and that Penny Bell later
asked for help in finding someone to kill her husband, sheriff's Lt.
Gary Cuff testified Monday.
   Deputies then hid a microphone on another informant, and Cuff
said deputies listened as family members admitted to the murder
plot. Robert Dow Bell said that Patricia had ``the guts to do it''
and fired the shot, Cuff said.
   Ms. Hylton and her brother were jailed without bail. Bail for
Penny Bell was set at $400,000.
</TEXT>
