<SECOND>AM-BRF--SAfrica-Mine,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>11 Miners Killed in Accident; 3 Missing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JOHANNESBURG, South Africa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A shower of rocks in a gold
mine west of Johannesburg killed 11 miners and left three missing,
authorities said Tuesday.
   Six men also suffered injuries at the West Driefontein mine
Monday in a ``pressure burst'' _ an accident caused when a buildup
of underground pressure erupts through the face of a mine shaft or
tunnel, according to Gold Fields of South Africa, owner of the
facility.
   The accident occurred at nearly 7,600 feet underground.
   The company said efforts to find the missing miners were
continuing.
   South Africa has many of the deepest gold mines in the world and
hundreds of miners are killed in underground accidents each year.
</TEXT>
