<HEAD>With AM-South Africa, Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oliver Tambo, president of the African National
Congress, is resting in a hospital after collapsing from exhaustion,
a spokesman said Tuesday.
   Tambo, 71, was flown to London Friday for medical tests.
   The exiled South African nationalist leader was was suffering
from exhaustion brought on by a punishing schedule, said Mendi
Msimang, the ANC's chief representative in London, who visited him
Monday night.
