<SECOND>AM-Afghanistan,0275</SECOND>
<HEAD>18 Rockets Hit Kabul and Airport</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By EDITH M. LEDERER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>KABUL, Afghanistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eighteen rockets hit Kabul's airport
and residential areas Tuesday, killing and wounding some civilians,
the government said.
   Foreign Ministry spokesman Mohammad Nabi Amani said there were
civilian casualties but he had no figures. He said there were no
casualties at the airport but sources there said a soldier was
