<SECOND>AM-Parties-Finances,100</SECOND>
<HEAD>Republicans Far Ahead of Democrats in Fund-Raising</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Half a year after renewing its lease on the
White House, the Republican Party has a 5-to-1 financial advantage
over the Democrats, according to a report Tuesday by the Federal
Election Commission.
   During the first six months of the year, the national committees
of the Republican Party raised a total of more than $45 million,
while the Democrats raised just $8.9 million, the report said.
   In the same period, Republicans also outspent the Democrats $36.4
million to $10.1 million.
   The Republicans have held similar financial advantages in the
comparable periods following the 1984 and 1986 elections, the
commission report said.
