<FIRST>r f AM-Earns-SaraLee     08-15 0255</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Earns-Sara Lee,0263</SECOND>
<HEAD>Sara Lee Posts Record Sales, Earnings for Quarter and Year</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Sara Lee Corp. on Tuesday announced record
fourth-quarter sales of $3.06 billion and earnings of $102.7
million, led by strong performances by the hosiery and underwear
companies in its personal-products division.
   The sales figure represented a 5.5 percent increase over the $2.9
billion recorded in the year-earlier period, while earnings were up
17.9 percent over the $87.1 million logged in the final quarter of
1988. Per-share earnings rose to 86 cents from 75 cents.
   For the fiscal year ended July 1, sales were $11.7 billion, a
12.4 percent increase from $10.4 billion in 1988, and net income
rose 26.3 percent to $410.5 million from last year's $325.1 million.
Earnings per share to $3.50 from $2.83 a year earlier.
   While most consumers still associate the Chicago-based
conglomerate with pastries, the Sara Lee bakery division showed only
a 6 percent increase in volume for the year.
   By comparison, sales were up 20 percent and earnings 28 percent
for the personal products division, led by such companies as Haines
Underwear and L'eggs hosiery.
   ``That wouldn't come as a surprise to market analysts or the
investment community,'' said company spokesman Ronald Culp. ``That's
been the area of strongest growth in recent years.''
   The fiscal-year earnings also reflected a pretax gain of
approximately $87 million as Sara Lee sold its Hollywood Brands,
Lyon's and Peck Foods subsidiaries. Earnings also were affected by a
$55 million charge for restructuring of the U.S. food operations.
</TEXT>
