<FILEID>AP-NR-08-15-89 1659EDT</FILEID>
<FIRST>r f AM-Gannett     08-15 0173</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Gannett,0180</SECOND>
<HEAD>Publishers Named in Little Rock, Fort Myers, Gainesville, Ga.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The appointment of Craig A. Moon to be
president and publisher of the Arkansas Gazette in Little Rock was
announced Tuesday by Gannett Co. among a number of management
changes in its newspaper division.
   Moon comes to the Gazette from the Fort Myers (Fla.) News-Press,
where he held comparable jobs. He succeeds William T. Malone, who
replaces Hugh B. Patterson Jr., as chairman. Patterson becomes
chairman emeritus.
   Dan A. Martin succeeds Moon as president and publisher of the
Fort Myers newspaper and is, in turn, succeeded by Denise H.
Bannister as president and publisher of the Huntington (W.Va.)
Herald-Dispatch.
   Bannister, currently president and publisher of the Times in
Gainesville, Ga., is being succeeded in that position by William V.
Monopoli, previously publisher of the Suburban Newspaper Group in
Cherry Hill, N.J.
   David J. Mack, president and publisher of the Press &amp;
Sun-Bulletin in Binghamton, N.Y., assumes additional duties as a
regional vice president in the Gannett East Group.
</TEXT>
